President Trump provided an update on the COVID-19 pandemic and the state of the economy during a press conference held at the Trump National Golf Club in Bedminster, New Jersey. He highlighted the decline in COVID-19 cases and hospitalizations, as well as the success of the testing program in the United States. The President also emphasized the rapid economic recovery, citing retail spending, auto production, and small business optimism as positive indicators. He expressed his support for college football to resume and criticized the NBA for their handling of the national anthem protests. President Trump addressed concerns about the postal service and mail-in voting, stating that he supports funding for the postal service but opposes universal mail-in voting. He also discussed his stance on Chinese tech companies, such as Huawei, and mentioned the possibility of pardoning Edward Snowden. The President expressed confidence in Defense Secretary Mark Esper and discussed the enthusiasm for his re-election campaign.